 ethnic Chinese and non-Chinese, the volume also explores the position of the ethnic Chinese in contemporary as well as the future Southeast Asia, providing readers with a most up-to-date and comprehensive study on the subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aAdam, Ahmat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeng, Tan Chee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChantavanich, Supang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahana, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGungwu, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHing, Lee Kam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhanh, Tran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKong, Chiew Seen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKyi, Khin Maung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMani, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhuong,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSee, Teresita Ang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuryadinata, Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuryadinata, Leo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTan, Mely G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTan, Mely, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThan, Mya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVelasco, Renato S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAs